cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CL

This paper is about instance segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel approach that learns intermediate concepts to address the problem of generalization in instance segmentation, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of TPUs, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics) as well. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of embeddings, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
